addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[p(x)=c(x-\alpha _{1})(…)(x-\alpha _{n})]]></fr:tex>
be the factorization of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex> over the splitting field. Then by the product rule for differentiation,
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[p'(x)=c\left (\frac {p(x)}{x-\alpha _{1}}+\frac {p(x)}{x-\alpha _{2}}+…+\frac {p(x)}{x-\alpha _{n}}\right ).]]></fr:tex>
We see each term in the sum is a polynomial.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longleftarrow )]]></fr:tex> (<fr:link
type="local"
href="nst-002I.xml"
addr="nst-002I"
title="Proof by contrapositive">Proof by contrapositive</fr:link>.) If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex> is inseparable, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{i}=\alpha _{j}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i\neq  j]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{i}]]></fr:tex> is a root of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)/(x-\alpha _{k})]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>, hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p'(\alpha _{i})=0]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{i}]]></fr:tex> is a common root of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p'(x)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longrightarrow )]]></fr:tex> (<fr:link
type="local"
href="nst-002G.xml"
addr="nst-002G"
title="Direct proof">Direct proof</fr:link>.) Assume <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex> is separable over its splitting field, then we see its roots satisfy <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{i}-\alpha _{j}\neq 0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i\neq  j]]></fr:tex>. Then we see
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[p'(\alpha _{i})=c\prod _{i\neq  j}(\alpha _{i}-\alpha _{j}),]]></fr:tex>
so that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{i}]]></fr:tex> is not a root of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p'(x)]]></fr:tex>. Hence the result.</fr:p><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 

 
   
